JOHANNESBURG - Residents of Eldorado Park, south of Johannesburg, say drug abuse is destroying the most vulnerable in their community. Five young children – one only a month old – were recently rescued from a drug house. Many say authorities are ignoring their pleas for help. READ: Eldos drug syndicate cracked The social development department insists it's not turning a blind eye to the problem. It says it’s assisting the children and have moved them to relatives. * Watch the full video report by Khayelihle Khumalo in the gallery above. eNCA